				<li id="16558540" class="cmnt-root" data="30" data-d="1647949972000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580097/Magic-Scorpion-Charm" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">22 Mar 2022 07:52</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16558540" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">So I managed to successfully get this talisman and complete Rannis quest line without requiring Celestial Dew to reset any NPC aggro at the church of vows.<br/><br/>Basically these are the steps I followed, some may be able to be skipped but if you want to be thorough then I suggest following along.<br/><br/>1. Met Blaidd at Mistwood Ruins by using the finger snap<br/>2. Killed Bloodhound Knight at Forlorn Hound Evergaol and talked to Blaidd afterwards<br/>3. Completed Carina Manor and started Rannis quest line by speaking to her, Seluvis, Iji and Blaidd.<br/>4. Met with Blaidd in the Siofra River<br/>5. Talked to Seluvis and got the potion to give to Nepheli.<br/>6. Took the potion to Gideon and had him pour it out, could have given to Nepheli but I also wanted to see the new changes to her quest line on this playthrough.<br/>6. Returned to Seluvis and got the introduction to Sellens.<br/>6. Met with Sellens<br/>7. Returned to Rannis tower, opened Seluvis underground puppet room and confronted him about it.<br/>8. Took the Jarwight puppet from Seluvis (this one costs 3 starlight shards to buy otherwise).<br/>9. Bought out the rest of his inventory for spells and then bought another puppet from him.  After buying the puppet he will let you in on a scheme to make Ranni into a puppet and ask you to retrieve the Amber Starlight.<br/>10. I retrieved the amber starlight from Altus Plateau and returned it to him.  He then gives the scorpion charm to you at this point.  I did not talk to him again so I never got any additional dialogue about the potion for Ranni.<br/><br/>I was then able to progress through the rest of Rannis quest normally by killing Radahn, going into Nokron and retrieving the fingerprint blade and then eventually going through nokstella and the lake of rot to the plateau in Liurnia to talk to her.  She did not become hostile to me at any point during the quest.  Good luck to anyone else trying to get this talisman, it seems like this quest is so easy to mess up on accident.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16558540" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16558540" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>31</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16558540"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16558540" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16558540"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
