				<li id="16490667" class="cmnt-root" data="55" data-d="1646990087000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=130401" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">Twht</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580097/Magic-Scorpion-Charm" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">11 Mar 2022 04:14</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16490667" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This is how I successfully obtained this item on a fresh new game+.<br/><br/>1. Progress normally and kill Margit.<br/><br/>2. Speak with Nepheli Loux outside of the Godrick fight and summon her before killing the boss.<br/><br/>3. Speak with Nepheli inside the round table and exhaust her dialog. She mentions speaking to her father Gideon Ofnir in his study. To unlock this study speak with finger Reader Enia in the room with Two Fingers at the round table.<br/><br/>4. Exhaust Gideon&apos;s dialogue about Nepheli. At this point Nepheli left the round table and is under the bridge at the Village of the Albinaurics.<br/><br/>5. Travel to the Village of the Albinaurics and exhaust her dialogue. Go through the village and kill the Omenkiller side boss.<br/><br/>6. Prior to going back to the round table progress through the lakes up to Ranni&apos;s Rise. Begin Ranni&apos;s questline and head to Seluvis&apos;s Rise. Speak with Seluvis and accept his quest to give the potion to Nepheli.<br/><br/>7. Return to the round table and Nephili will be at the bottom of the stairs near the blacksmith in her depressing state.<br/><br/>8. Speak with Gideon about Nepheli, don&apos;t tell him about the potion Seluvis gives you. Return to Nepheli exhaust her dialogue which ends in giving her the potion.<br/><br/>9. Return to Ranni&apos;s Rise and enter into Seluvis&apos;s Puppet Room. This is located in the ruins to the north east of Ranni&apos;s tower. It is underneath a hidden wall/floor you have to hit to open. Interact with the message in the back right of the room which says Seluvis Puppet do not touch.<br/><br/>10. Return to Seluvis and exhaust the dialogue reference his puppet room. He will let you buy a puppet.<br/><br/>11. Buy all the sorceries Seluvis has in stock and rest at a grace. After returning to Seluvis there is a dialogue option about his scheme.<br/><br/>12. Obtain the Amber Starlight in Altus Plateau. It is located in the valley to the west of the Stormcaller Church. (You can access the Altus Plateau without the lift key if you progress through the river at the top of the lakes and go through the Ruin-Stern Precipice sub area.<br/><br/>13. Return to Seluvis and give him the Amber Starlight. Speak with him again and he will give you the Magic Scorpion Charm.<br/><br/>(Things to consider)<br/><br/>A lot of misinformation on what is required to get this item. I didn&apos;t kill Rennala Queen of the Full Moon. I didn&apos;t kill Starscourge Radahn.<br/>Additional note, Seluvis&apos;s scheme does ruin Rannis questline. So if you have to choose which one you want to do. This is what worked for me to obtain this item, it is possible I took unneeded steps. Enjoy the bonus magic damage!</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16490667" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16490667" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">4</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>58</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>3</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16490667"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16490667" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16490667"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16490589" class="cmnt-root" data="35" data-d="1646989874000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t580097/Magic-Scorpion-Charm" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">11 Mar 2022 04:11</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16490589" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Godammit FS cryptic quests. Just google&apos;d to see if there&apos;s some good magic tali, found that one, yet i have finished Ranni&apos;s quest before 2h..</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16490589" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16490589" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>39</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>4</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16490589"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16490589" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/